WEBVTT

00:17.234 --> 00:21.412
[stormy,
nature sounds with drums]

00:38.125 --> 00:43.043
[speaking in alien language]

00:43.086 --> 00:45.436
[funky music]

00:45.480 --> 00:46.350
♪ Hey. Hey.

00:46.394 --> 00:47.438
♪ What's up?

00:47.482 --> 00:49.179
♪ Hey, what's up?
Not much. ♪

00:49.223 --> 00:54.054
[music continues
with a woosh sound]

00:55.098 --> 00:58.710
♪ There's beauty above you

00:58.754 --> 01:03.193
♪ There's beauty below

01:03.237 --> 01:07.110
♪ Beauty surrounds you

01:07.154 --> 01:11.723
♪ Everywhere you go

01:11.767 --> 01:15.162
♪ If you've got a mind to

01:15.205 --> 01:19.296
♪ set your dreams in a word

01:20.297 --> 01:24.388
♪ You've got the power

01:24.432 --> 01:28.610
♪ to rock this world

01:28.653 --> 01:33.571
♪ You gotta have
faith, hope, charity

01:33.615 --> 01:38.098
♪ You gotta trust in yourself
and what you can't see

01:38.141 --> 01:42.798
♪ On a city street
or an older road ♪

01:44.800 --> 01:47.237
♪ You got the power

01:47.281 --> 01:50.022
[traffic noises]

02:02.687 --> 02:06.865
♪ This ain't a rich
man or a poor man ♪

02:08.215 --> 02:11.870
♪ They grow and leave

02:11.914 --> 02:16.919
♪ You can be a doctor,
or a lawyer ♪

02:17.746 --> 02:19.487
♪ Even a tribal chief

02:19.530 --> 02:21.532
[chuckling]
Look at you, all serious.

02:26.189 --> 02:28.278
RINGO:
I'm glad we're doing
this together.

02:28.322 --> 02:31.542
Like it's really great for
my Social Linguistics class.

02:31.586 --> 02:35.024
This semester I'm
concentrating on field work.

02:36.199 --> 02:38.549
MITZI:
Is that all you think about?

02:38.593 --> 02:40.247
Not always.

02:43.206 --> 02:46.122
I have some questions
I wanted to ask you

02:46.166 --> 02:47.645
for my next paper.

02:47.689 --> 02:49.212
Mitzi:
I don't think so.

02:49.256 --> 02:51.780
I'm your girlfriend,
not your subject.

02:55.697 --> 02:57.699
What's your thesis
called again?

02:58.265 --> 03:00.658
"Indian Moves to
the Big City"?

03:00.702 --> 03:02.834
"The Urbanization of
the Native Population

03:02.878 --> 03:04.358
"in North America".

03:04.401 --> 03:05.359
[Mitzi laughing]

03:05.402 --> 03:07.709
You and your field work.

03:10.102 --> 03:12.409
I don't want to be studied.

03:14.585 --> 03:16.065
I'm gonna make hats.

03:17.022 --> 03:20.591
Crazy, wacky, out
of this world hats.

03:20.635 --> 03:23.203
Hats that are gonna
save the world.

03:23.246 --> 03:25.901
How are hats gonna
save the world?

03:29.600 --> 03:32.647
One sandwich at a time.

03:33.082 --> 03:36.216
And where are these world
saving hats coming from?

03:36.259 --> 03:38.218
From me.

03:38.261 --> 03:40.394
I'm applying to
fashion design school.

03:40.437 --> 03:43.135
I'm gonna make life
saving headgear

03:43.179 --> 03:45.660
like you would not believe.

03:45.703 --> 03:49.011
I'm gonna need a portfolio.

03:49.054 --> 03:53.494
So could you take
some photos for me?

03:53.537 --> 03:54.973
[laughing]

03:55.017 --> 03:58.586
And are we still going dancing
after for my birthday?

03:58.629 --> 04:00.631
RINGO:
You only turn 25 once.

04:02.198 --> 04:04.026
I know this crazy
crowded dance club.

04:05.810 --> 04:07.290
The DJ is my friend.

04:07.682 --> 04:09.336
Everybody's your friend.

04:09.379 --> 04:11.816
Ah, you know it, huh?

04:11.860 --> 04:13.078
[laughing]

04:14.732 --> 04:15.994
Okay.

04:23.654 --> 04:24.873
Here you go, guys.

04:27.223 --> 04:28.659
Here you go.

04:28.703 --> 04:30.182
RINGO:
You get a hat.

04:30.226 --> 04:31.619
You get a hat.

04:32.359 --> 04:33.577
You get a hat.

04:35.884 --> 04:37.102
[horn honking]

05:14.618 --> 05:16.316
MITZI:
Hey, Charlie B.

05:18.492 --> 05:20.145
How you doing?

05:21.233 --> 05:23.235
What is it now?

05:24.236 --> 05:25.412
Asthma?

05:26.543 --> 05:28.284
Bronchitis?

05:28.328 --> 05:29.720
Pneumonia?

05:31.069 --> 05:32.506
Emphysema?

05:32.549 --> 05:34.551
Tuberculosis?

05:35.422 --> 05:37.424
Asbestos?

05:42.385 --> 05:44.561
Where'd the green giant go?

05:44.605 --> 05:47.042
Ringo took me
dancing last night.

05:47.085 --> 05:48.739
My legs are still aching.

05:48.783 --> 05:50.785
What's his last
name again?

05:51.525 --> 05:53.178
Leaves-No-Tip?

05:53.918 --> 05:55.485
Leaves-No-Shadow.

05:56.443 --> 05:59.402
CHARLIE B:
Does he still go on like,

05:59.446 --> 06:01.926
"On my reservation-

06:01.970 --> 06:03.972
and blah, blah, blah.

06:05.103 --> 06:06.801
He's proud of where
he comes from.

06:06.844 --> 06:09.107
You should try and
be his friend.

06:09.151 --> 06:13.155
His droll academic
dialogue bores me.

06:13.851 --> 06:15.418
I could never be his friend.

06:15.462 --> 06:17.289
Some people like their home.

06:20.597 --> 06:22.425
You hear from teachers' college?

06:22.469 --> 06:24.035
I start in the fall.

06:27.561 --> 06:29.780
But I have to get in
better shape first.

06:47.494 --> 06:50.584
Did you hear from Uncle William

06:50.627 --> 06:52.847
and Auntie Annabelle?

06:52.890 --> 06:54.152
No.

06:56.416 --> 06:58.374
I only hear from them
when someone's dead

06:58.418 --> 07:00.550
or if they need me to
send them something.

07:02.552 --> 07:05.033
At least you have parents.

07:05.076 --> 07:06.338
Crazy.

07:07.252 --> 07:08.863
They're your parents too.

07:09.472 --> 07:11.343
They brought you up, remember?

07:12.083 --> 07:14.042
You're kind of my brother.

07:19.177 --> 07:21.005
I wish I had a mom.

07:25.488 --> 07:27.621
You can have mine.

07:27.664 --> 07:29.013
Oh, I forgot.

07:29.057 --> 07:30.667
You already do.

07:34.323 --> 07:36.281
Read something to me, Mitz.

07:44.028 --> 07:46.291
Next time, I gotta get home.

07:50.426 --> 07:52.428
I have a ton of work to do.

07:53.908 --> 07:57.912
[somber music]

08:07.661 --> 08:11.708
♪ music continues

08:41.608 --> 08:43.044
He looks bad.

08:43.261 --> 08:44.567
He'll survive.

08:44.611 --> 08:46.482
He always does.

09:27.392 --> 09:31.222
Molly, can't you or Blabby
go help Dad with Mom?

09:33.442 --> 09:35.400
What do you mean I'm selfish?

09:38.621 --> 09:39.927
It's my turn?

09:39.970 --> 09:41.929
I have things to do.

09:41.972 --> 09:43.017
[phone clicks]

09:43.060 --> 09:44.540
Hello?

09:44.584 --> 09:45.628
[dial tone buzzing]

09:45.672 --> 09:47.021
Hello?

09:48.675 --> 09:50.502
Ringo:
There's gorgeous, gorgeous.

09:51.068 --> 09:53.157
Mitzi, your hats are fantastic.

09:53.201 --> 09:54.594
Really beautiful.

09:54.637 --> 09:56.204
Like out of this world.

09:56.247 --> 09:57.901
Oh I'm crazy about them.

09:58.641 --> 09:59.990
I'm gonna write an essay.

10:00.034 --> 10:04.125
With your hats and my photos,
no kidding,

10:04.168 --> 10:07.171
maybe you can even apply
to a school in Europe.

10:07.781 --> 10:10.958
[funky music]
[camera shutter clicking]

10:11.001 --> 10:12.176
Oh, oh.

10:12.220 --> 10:13.656
It's stuck. Ow.

10:13.700 --> 10:15.136
Ow ow ow ow.

10:15.179 --> 10:16.137
Oh, I'm stuck.

10:16.180 --> 10:17.138
Ow, I'm stuck.

10:17.181 --> 10:18.618
RINGO:
Hold still.

10:18.879 --> 10:20.445
Ow! Ow!

10:20.489 --> 10:22.665
Oh, are you okay?

10:22.796 --> 10:24.449
Just a prick.

10:24.754 --> 10:26.843
We must sacrifice for our art.

10:28.105 --> 10:29.367
Okay, all right.

10:29.672 --> 10:31.369
What a great afternoon.

10:32.632 --> 10:35.025
You, me.

10:36.113 --> 10:39.116
My camera, your talent.

10:41.858 --> 10:42.990
Me.

10:43.033 --> 10:44.252
My rose prick.

10:48.125 --> 10:49.779
You've been quiet all day.

10:49.823 --> 10:52.086
Did I do something?

10:53.653 --> 10:58.179
[soft music]

10:58.222 --> 11:01.225
[camera shutter clicking]

11:06.796 --> 11:08.189
I have to go home.

11:08.232 --> 11:09.233
I have to go home.

11:09.277 --> 11:11.279
[crying] I have to go home.

11:11.888 --> 11:14.108
Aren't you home now?

11:17.154 --> 11:18.416
No.

11:20.549 --> 11:22.682
I have to go back
home to my reserve,

11:22.725 --> 11:24.422
Crazy Owl Island.

11:24.466 --> 11:25.946
The place where
everyone's cuckoo

11:25.989 --> 11:28.252
and no one wants to live there,
including me.

11:28.296 --> 11:30.690
It can't be that bad, can it?

11:30.733 --> 11:32.300
No, it is that bad.

11:35.738 --> 11:38.872
Everyone on that island
is a little off.

11:38.915 --> 11:41.918
RINGO:
Everyone feels that
way about their home.

11:43.790 --> 11:45.269
Maybe it's changed.

11:45.879 --> 11:46.923
Is there wifi?

11:46.967 --> 11:48.708
Maybe I could do
some research there.

11:48.751 --> 11:50.100
We're like a pack
of werewolves,

11:50.144 --> 11:52.102
or some other group of losers.

11:52.146 --> 11:53.364
What?

11:53.930 --> 11:55.584
Somebody die?

12:02.634 --> 12:03.984
It's my Dad.

12:05.942 --> 12:07.335
It's my Mom.

12:10.686 --> 12:13.471
My Dad needs my help
to look after her.

12:13.515 --> 12:15.343
She's sick.

12:17.388 --> 12:22.350
[gentle music]

12:22.393 --> 12:26.702
♪ music continues

12:26.746 --> 12:28.356
It's rough.

12:31.098 --> 12:32.708
It's really nice of your Dad

12:32.752 --> 12:34.579
to send you a birthday present.

12:34.623 --> 12:36.668
No, I don't want to go back.

12:37.278 --> 12:41.064
My mom hates everyone
except my cousin.

12:42.849 --> 12:45.025
Why does everything
have to happen to me?

12:45.068 --> 12:49.333
And fashion school,
you're coming back, right?

12:49.377 --> 12:50.639
And us.

12:50.682 --> 12:52.510
There is no us.

12:58.778 --> 13:00.649
My island sucks.

13:03.391 --> 13:04.784
WOMAN:
Hey, Honeyboy.

13:04.827 --> 13:06.611
Can you give us a
lift to Owl Island?

13:06.655 --> 13:08.352
Shouldn't you girls
be in school?

13:08.396 --> 13:09.789
WOMAN:
Ah, come on.

13:09.832 --> 13:11.007
You can party with us.

13:11.051 --> 13:12.661
We made sandwiches.

13:12.704 --> 13:14.315
We have weed.

13:14.358 --> 13:15.838
I have work to do.

13:15.882 --> 13:17.840
You should be
learning something.

13:17.884 --> 13:19.363
Come on, I'll give
you a ride home.

13:19.407 --> 13:20.843
Let's go.

13:20.887 --> 13:24.847
[funky instrumental]

13:28.895 --> 13:33.595
♪ music continues

13:35.336 --> 13:36.772
I remember being that age.

13:36.816 --> 13:39.427
Nothing to do but
make trouble.

13:39.470 --> 13:41.516
Life here is short and cold.

13:41.559 --> 13:44.562
They're just trying real
hard to have a life.

13:52.440 --> 13:55.051
I can't believe you're
still driving this boat.

13:55.095 --> 13:57.314
I thought you would've
left the island by now.

13:58.925 --> 14:01.536
Still gathering medicine
for your grandfather?

14:01.579 --> 14:04.582
HONEYBOY:
Yeah, when he goes out in
the Bush with your dad,

14:04.626 --> 14:06.454
I go with them.

14:09.370 --> 14:11.198
You haven't been around
here in a while either.

14:11.241 --> 14:14.070
My presence has
been requested.

14:14.592 --> 14:16.246
They still call you Honeyboy?

14:16.290 --> 14:17.900
Uh, yeah.

14:17.944 --> 14:19.728
You remember Simone Muskrat?

14:19.771 --> 14:22.731
Hey, Simone,
you remember Mitzi Bearclaw?

14:22.774 --> 14:25.777
[quirky jazzy instrumental]

14:29.999 --> 14:32.393
What a stupid looking hat.

14:32.436 --> 14:35.439
[quirky jazzy instrumental]

14:38.442 --> 14:42.490
♪ music continues

14:42.533 --> 14:44.492
You're still a muskrat.

14:44.535 --> 14:48.061
[clears throat and horks]

14:48.104 --> 14:51.934
[quirky jazzy instrumental]

14:55.982 --> 15:00.290
♪ music continues

15:05.034 --> 15:06.470
[horn honking]

15:17.177 --> 15:19.831
William will come by
to pick these up later.

15:19.875 --> 15:21.877
Good to know we have
drinking water.

15:24.271 --> 15:26.882
[horn blowing]

15:26.926 --> 15:28.753
You've got a wild one there.

15:28.797 --> 15:30.755
Muskrat's still wreaking
havoc in the streets?

15:30.799 --> 15:32.192
[horn blowing]

15:33.671 --> 15:35.673
She really likes
blowing that horn.

15:36.848 --> 15:38.981
Yeah, she does.

15:39.025 --> 15:42.985
Any chance she's going
away somewhere forever?

16:05.573 --> 16:06.791
[distant horn blowing]

16:09.185 --> 16:12.188
[distant dog barking]

16:15.975 --> 16:18.978
[wind chimes chiming]
[leaves rustling]

16:22.807 --> 16:25.810
[somber spiritual humming]

16:32.817 --> 16:36.386
[Angelic Harmonies]

17:07.113 --> 17:10.420
[wind blowing]
[wind chimes chiming]

17:10.464 --> 17:14.468
[somber spiritual humming]

17:16.470 --> 17:20.474
[Angelic Harmonies]

17:23.868 --> 17:27.089
[uptempo song on radio]

17:34.314 --> 17:35.924
Mitzi.

17:35.967 --> 17:39.058
Oh, I thought I heard
Yellowdog's boat.

17:39.101 --> 17:41.930
You're not supposed to
be here until next week.

17:41.973 --> 17:44.019
Dad, it is next week.

17:44.063 --> 17:45.934
Ah, I was gonna
clean up this mess

17:45.977 --> 17:47.675
right after I finished
reading last week's news.

17:47.718 --> 17:49.372
Dad.

17:50.112 --> 17:51.461
It's okay.

17:51.505 --> 17:53.115
Don't do that.

17:59.034 --> 18:00.470
Where's Mom?

18:00.862 --> 18:02.081
WILLIAM: In bed.

18:02.124 --> 18:04.083
She might be awake.

18:04.126 --> 18:05.649
That horn would
wake anybody up.

18:05.693 --> 18:07.434
I saw Charlie B
at the hospital.

18:07.477 --> 18:09.088
He's coming home soon.

18:10.176 --> 18:11.699
How's she doing?

18:11.742 --> 18:13.135
Not too good.

18:15.529 --> 18:18.271
The doctors say they can't
do anything else for her.

18:18.314 --> 18:21.143
She'll-she'll be going
on dialysis soon.

18:23.319 --> 18:25.060
One day she'll
leave this island

18:25.104 --> 18:27.106
and never come back again.

18:29.717 --> 18:31.675
What's her mood been like?

18:31.719 --> 18:34.678
Miserable, hateful, the usual.

18:35.375 --> 18:37.812
Why do you think your
sisters wouldn't come?

18:37.855 --> 18:41.555
You, I wouldn't have written
to you if I had a choice.

18:41.598 --> 18:43.513
If only Charlie B was around,

18:43.557 --> 18:45.298
she'd be nicer.

18:45.341 --> 18:47.474
She treats him
like a bear cub.

18:47.517 --> 18:49.171
How can you stand it?

18:49.215 --> 18:50.694
You get used to it.

18:50.738 --> 18:52.479
She's in pain.

18:52.522 --> 18:54.655
If I could take it
from her I would.

18:55.525 --> 18:57.658
She's suffered enough.

19:01.792 --> 19:03.664
Dad, I'm sorry.

19:04.360 --> 19:06.406
[crying]

19:06.449 --> 19:08.451
It's gonna be fine.

19:10.627 --> 19:12.977
ANNABELLE: William!
Talking to yourself?

19:13.021 --> 19:14.196
Knock it off.

19:14.240 --> 19:15.763
You're sounding crazy.

19:15.806 --> 19:17.765
Hope you're not
PTSD'ing again.

19:17.808 --> 19:19.201
Can't help you this time.

19:19.245 --> 19:21.160
WILLIAM:
The bear has awakened.

19:22.944 --> 19:24.206
Any coffee?

19:24.250 --> 19:25.729
Yeah.

19:32.040 --> 19:33.563
Want any?

19:33.607 --> 19:36.305
No, I better not.
I had three already.

19:36.349 --> 19:38.220
I think I'm getting an ulcer.

19:41.354 --> 19:43.182
Ah, it's pretty bad.

19:43.225 --> 19:44.357
How long has it been there?

19:44.400 --> 19:45.749
Uh, just this morning.

19:46.272 --> 19:47.403
I like it strong.

19:49.405 --> 19:51.407
You're not used to
bush coffee anymore.

19:54.236 --> 19:56.369
Go in and say hi
to your mother.

19:56.412 --> 19:58.893
I'll let you two have
some time alone.

19:58.936 --> 20:02.375
I think I may be going out
for a while with Oliver.

20:02.418 --> 20:04.377
We want to go do some hunting.

20:04.420 --> 20:07.597
I keep telling him that
there's nothing left to hunt,

20:07.641 --> 20:08.816
but he doesn't care.

20:08.859 --> 20:10.557
Dad, that letter you sent me

20:10.600 --> 20:13.473
made it sound like
Mom was dying.

20:13.516 --> 20:16.345
I didn't know what to expect.

20:16.389 --> 20:20.262
I guess I over exaggerated.

20:20.306 --> 20:22.264
It sounded desperate.

20:22.308 --> 20:23.874
I'm sorry.

20:25.441 --> 20:27.443
I really missed you.

20:30.881 --> 20:33.406
ANNABELLE:
William, quit
talking to yourself.

20:33.449 --> 20:34.842
Is Molly here?

20:36.626 --> 20:38.237
Go in and say hi.

20:40.761 --> 20:42.371
[knocking]

20:43.416 --> 20:46.245
["This Ole House"
by Stuart Hamblen]

20:46.288 --> 20:47.637
Hi, Ma.

20:53.774 --> 20:55.471
What are you doing here?

20:56.342 --> 20:58.735
Come to see me die?

20:58.779 --> 21:00.868
Can't wait, can ya?

21:03.218 --> 21:05.351
Ma, can't you even say hi?

21:05.394 --> 21:06.656
Hello.

21:07.091 --> 21:08.484
Now get lost.

21:10.921 --> 21:13.272
[sniffling]

21:13.315 --> 21:14.838
Why do you have
to be like that?

21:14.882 --> 21:16.840
Why'd you come back?

21:16.884 --> 21:18.842
Run out of money?

21:18.886 --> 21:21.323
Well I don't have any and
neither does your Dad.

21:21.367 --> 21:23.107
Just like your sisters.

21:23.151 --> 21:26.197
I thought I was done having
kids and then you came along.

21:27.460 --> 21:28.983
Why does everything
have to happen to me?

21:29.026 --> 21:30.332
I thought that things
might've changed.

21:30.376 --> 21:31.681
I see they haven't.

21:31.725 --> 21:33.335
Why should they, huh?

21:33.379 --> 21:34.902
Life is just peachy.

21:37.557 --> 21:39.036
Radio Announcer: And now for our next selection.

21:39.080 --> 21:41.735
Words come easy.

21:41.778 --> 21:45.304
[by The Glaser Brothers]

21:45.347 --> 21:47.306
♪ Words come easy

21:47.349 --> 21:49.308
It's so stuffy in here.

21:52.354 --> 21:55.314
What are you trying to do,
kill me?

21:55.357 --> 21:57.054
It's freezing cold out there.

21:57.577 --> 21:59.535
Close that damn window.

22:01.232 --> 22:05.324
[slow country music]

22:05.367 --> 22:07.935
Who else looks after
you besides Dad, huh?

22:08.196 --> 22:09.632
Just your Dad.

22:11.286 --> 22:15.290
One year when your Dad was
going through a rough time

22:17.771 --> 22:22.384
I even went hunting on my
own with the other two.

22:23.777 --> 22:28.347
We skinned and packed the
animal all by ourselves.

22:28.390 --> 22:29.609
Didn't need any help then

22:29.652 --> 22:32.568
and I still don't need
any help right now!

22:38.182 --> 22:40.620
If I wasn't sick I
could do everything.

22:40.663 --> 22:42.099
Now look at me.

22:45.451 --> 22:46.974
MITZI:
Where's Molly and Blabby?

22:47.017 --> 22:48.410
Don't they come here?

22:48.454 --> 22:50.586
They got their own families.

22:50.630 --> 22:52.327
Besides, they're all stupid.

22:54.938 --> 22:57.767
William, get in here!

23:00.553 --> 23:02.076
I'm here.

23:02.119 --> 23:03.686
Our girl is finally home.

23:04.121 --> 23:05.514
I need help!

23:05.558 --> 23:07.473
Mitzi can help you.

23:09.823 --> 23:11.999
She's as useless as
the rest of them.

23:13.479 --> 23:17.613
Probably still trying to
become something really fancy.

23:20.050 --> 23:22.052
How's your dress making going?

23:23.489 --> 23:25.099
I make hats.

23:25.752 --> 23:28.885
Shut the damn window,
hat maker.

23:30.452 --> 23:32.280
It seems like a waste to me.

23:33.412 --> 23:34.848
You're hopeless.

23:50.341 --> 23:53.170
♪ Ooh

23:54.650 --> 23:57.436
♪ Ooh wee

23:57.479 --> 24:01.483
Welcome home,
Mitzi Bearclaw.

24:01.527 --> 24:03.485
Oh, I had forgotten about you.

24:03.529 --> 24:05.182
[soft spiritual humming]

24:05.226 --> 24:06.488
The others?

24:06.532 --> 24:09.491
Faith and Charity
were right behind me.

24:15.497 --> 24:17.325
What do you wanna do?

24:17.368 --> 24:19.240
You can go anywhere.

24:19.283 --> 24:21.155
I wish I could go anywhere.

24:21.198 --> 24:22.765
Anywhere but here.

24:23.026 --> 24:25.464
WILLIAM:
The future is the
only place to go.

24:25.507 --> 24:28.205
You just have to keep moving
and then you're there.

24:29.076 --> 24:32.340
It'll get better,
I promise.

24:32.383 --> 24:36.213
[soft spiritual humming]

24:36.257 --> 24:37.301
[growling]

24:37.345 --> 24:39.086
What the hell was that?

24:39.129 --> 24:40.304
[laughing]

24:40.348 --> 24:42.176
Charity is a trickster.

24:42.219 --> 24:44.526
He's just trying to
keep your guard up.

24:44.570 --> 24:46.746
WILLIAM:
He gets carried
away sometimes,

24:46.789 --> 24:49.270
but he won't harm you ever.

24:49.313 --> 24:50.401
[soft spiritual humming]

24:50.445 --> 24:51.490
[growling]

24:51.533 --> 24:52.752
No-

24:52.795 --> 24:54.797
When do you disappear?

24:55.624 --> 24:57.060
We.

24:58.061 --> 24:59.715
Are always.

25:00.977 --> 25:02.936
[chimes]

25:02.979 --> 25:06.461
♪ Happy

25:08.463 --> 25:11.901
[applause]

25:11.945 --> 25:14.774
[whimsical "Jingle Bells"]

25:14.817 --> 25:18.821
[dog barking in unison to song]

25:38.754 --> 25:39.929
[horn blowing]

25:40.930 --> 25:42.932
Smell that air.

25:44.760 --> 25:47.763
Hey, you almost look normal.

25:51.593 --> 25:52.812
Is that Honeyboy Yellowdog

25:52.855 --> 25:55.249
your new object
of desire now?

25:55.292 --> 25:56.729
He's cool.

25:56.772 --> 25:57.904
Shut up.

25:57.947 --> 25:59.340
He's got a girlfriend, eh?

25:59.383 --> 26:00.341
Big deal.

26:00.384 --> 26:01.516
Simone Muskrat.

26:01.560 --> 26:03.562
[clears throat and horks]

26:04.650 --> 26:07.522
She was reading one of those
gossipy magazines on the boat.

26:07.566 --> 26:09.132
I don't care.

26:09.176 --> 26:11.178
Oh, you care.

26:12.658 --> 26:13.615
[coughing]

26:13.659 --> 26:15.138
Ah, she's gross.

26:15.182 --> 26:16.792
Yeah, she is.

26:16.836 --> 26:18.489
Give it a rest.

26:22.537 --> 26:24.539
What do you got
in here, rocks?

26:25.671 --> 26:28.761
My computer, my journals,

26:28.804 --> 26:29.936
notebooks.

26:29.979 --> 26:32.286
Oh, and I did bring some rocks.

26:32.329 --> 26:34.331
Fossils I found on the beach.

26:34.636 --> 26:36.333
True witnesses of time passing.

26:36.377 --> 26:38.031
They'd have to be rocks.

26:38.074 --> 26:40.468
You couldn't scan them or-

26:40.511 --> 26:42.775
leave them where
you found them?

26:42.818 --> 26:47.040
[coughing]

26:47.083 --> 26:48.171
CHARLIE B: Ringo.

26:48.215 --> 26:49.172
[coughing]

26:49.216 --> 26:51.044
What, huh?

26:51.174 --> 26:53.699
Ringo Leaves-No-Shadow
left a shadow.

26:55.091 --> 26:56.527
I'm sorry.

27:00.227 --> 27:04.013
And keep your mouth
shut about Honeyboy.

27:04.057 --> 27:06.973
[whistling]

27:07.016 --> 27:08.844
Wow, look at this place.

27:10.237 --> 27:11.847
It was a disaster.

27:14.937 --> 27:15.895
Where's Uncle William?

27:15.938 --> 27:17.331
Hunting.

27:17.374 --> 27:18.593
It cheers him up.

27:18.637 --> 27:19.855
Hungry?

27:20.290 --> 27:21.552
Nah.

27:25.034 --> 27:25.992
Maybe.

27:26.035 --> 27:27.471
What do you got?

27:31.824 --> 27:35.044
He says there's nothing
to hunt anymore.

27:36.089 --> 27:38.439
He likes to spend time
by himself in the Bush.

27:41.877 --> 27:43.313
And how's Auntie?

27:45.098 --> 27:46.969
Some things never change.

27:47.709 --> 27:49.711
What's the doctors say?

27:49.755 --> 27:52.671
No jogging, no smoking,
the usual.

27:52.714 --> 27:54.281
Any singing allowed?

27:59.416 --> 28:03.420
[singing in foreign language]

28:08.425 --> 28:12.429
♪ continues

28:13.430 --> 28:16.433
[coughing]

28:21.743 --> 28:23.919
I guess singing's out too.

28:24.877 --> 28:26.705
[coughing]

28:26.748 --> 28:28.707
ANNABELLE:
What the hell is
going on out there?

28:28.750 --> 28:30.883
What's all that goddamn noise?

28:30.926 --> 28:32.406
Nothing, Ma.

28:32.449 --> 28:33.973
Shhh.

28:34.016 --> 28:36.062
ANNABELLE:
Knock it off then.
I'm trying to sleep.

28:36.105 --> 28:40.936
[laughing and coughing]

28:41.763 --> 28:43.330
I wanna see her.

28:43.591 --> 28:45.767
You always were a suck up.

28:56.125 --> 28:58.911
Ma, Ma, Ma.

28:58.954 --> 29:00.129
What?

29:00.695 --> 29:01.914
Look who's here.

29:01.957 --> 29:03.959
You know I can't
see a damn thing!

29:07.136 --> 29:08.747
Hello, Auntie Annabelle.

29:08.790 --> 29:11.793
Oh, my sweet nephew, come.

29:15.710 --> 29:17.233
CHARLIE B:
I missed you.

29:17.277 --> 29:20.454
ANNABELLE:
Mitzi, why didn't you
tell me he was home?

29:24.806 --> 29:26.982
You've been gone so long.

29:30.812 --> 29:34.642
But now I'm back for good.

29:34.685 --> 29:38.820
[somber instrumental]

29:38.864 --> 29:41.692
I haven't seen you
in such a long time.

29:42.041 --> 29:43.738
I missed you.

29:50.658 --> 29:52.834
CHARLIE B:
I finally finished university.

29:53.661 --> 29:55.794
I just want to write.

29:55.837 --> 29:58.231
There's so many stories
that I want to finish.

29:58.274 --> 30:00.842
And I brought you
an audiobook on CD.

30:00.886 --> 30:02.670
It's called,
"The English Patient"

30:02.713 --> 30:04.237
by Michael Ondaatje.

30:04.280 --> 30:06.543
I know that you liked reading.

30:06.587 --> 30:09.068
You used to read to
me all the time.

30:09.111 --> 30:11.853
You used to read me
your crazy stories.

30:11.897 --> 30:13.115
[laughing]

30:14.290 --> 30:15.726
CHARLIE B:
It was special.

30:21.689 --> 30:24.083
I'm ready to die, Charlie.

30:24.126 --> 30:25.867
I'm worthless.

30:25.911 --> 30:29.175
No, no, don't say that.

30:29.218 --> 30:30.654
We love you.

30:32.831 --> 30:35.050
I can't help William
or the girls anymore.

30:35.094 --> 30:36.922
It's the sugar.

30:39.576 --> 30:40.882
It takes everybody.

30:40.926 --> 30:45.408
[coughing]

30:47.410 --> 30:51.023
[soft spiritual flute music]

30:51.066 --> 30:53.199
You know, I've always
loved your stories

30:53.242 --> 30:54.461
and your poetry.

30:55.505 --> 30:57.464
Why don't you read
me something?

30:57.507 --> 30:59.031
What would you like to hear?

30:59.074 --> 31:00.467
Oh, I don't know.

31:01.772 --> 31:03.470
Your latest.

31:03.513 --> 31:07.517
[soft spiritual flute music]

31:12.522 --> 31:15.525
♪ music continues

31:33.935 --> 31:36.503
CHARLIE B:
Ghost Dance, 1890.

31:36.546 --> 31:38.809
Not that long ago.

31:38.853 --> 31:41.638
The real human beings
were in trouble.

31:41.682 --> 31:43.945
They prayed to their
ancestors for help.

31:43.989 --> 31:45.642
The ancestors answered.

31:48.036 --> 31:52.649
Your, our.

31:52.693 --> 31:55.522
Heartbeats must continue.

31:55.565 --> 32:00.570
Drumming, dancing, singing,
laughing, loving, and touching.

32:01.397 --> 32:02.790
Feeling the sun.

32:02.833 --> 32:04.139
Tasting the rain.

32:04.183 --> 32:05.619
Hearing the wind.

32:05.662 --> 32:07.795
Smelling your hair.

32:07.838 --> 32:11.842
Breathing, feeling, listening.

32:13.322 --> 32:17.848
That is what we have to
do everyday forever,

32:19.850 --> 32:21.635
for infinity.

32:21.678 --> 32:25.682
[soft spiritual instrumental]

32:27.684 --> 32:31.210
♪ music continues

32:31.253 --> 32:32.994
CHARLIE B:
And now,

32:33.038 --> 32:34.561
how about something
from your famous

32:34.604 --> 32:36.128
wiener sandwich anthology?

32:36.171 --> 32:37.346
[gasp]

32:42.003 --> 32:44.701
CHARLIE B:
1975, day one.

32:44.745 --> 32:49.706
[country music]

32:50.707 --> 32:54.624
♪ music continues

32:57.410 --> 32:59.151
What do I owe
you for the gas?

32:59.194 --> 33:00.413
STORE OWNER:
10 dollars.

33:04.547 --> 33:06.027
Hey.
-Hey.

33:06.071 --> 33:07.420
Where's Simone?

33:07.463 --> 33:09.465
She's out trapping
with her mother.

33:10.466 --> 33:11.641
[laughing]

33:11.685 --> 33:14.166
I didn't think she
was the outdoorsy type.

33:14.209 --> 33:16.168
Yeah, well they like
to snare rabbits

33:16.211 --> 33:18.039
and other small animals.

33:18.083 --> 33:19.693
Must be a mother
daughter thing then.

33:19.736 --> 33:21.782
Gets her off my Dad's
boat for a while.

33:21.825 --> 33:24.698
Honeyboy Yellowdog still
driving your Dad's boat.

33:24.741 --> 33:26.569
Only when he asks me to.

33:28.093 --> 33:31.270
If I asked you to
drive my boat would you?

33:31.313 --> 33:33.098
Well I didn't know
that you had a boat.

33:33.141 --> 33:35.187
Well I do, I just
don't take it out.

33:35.230 --> 33:36.797
Oh that's a shame.

33:36.840 --> 33:39.365
Boats are meant to be driven.

33:39.408 --> 33:41.280
What are you doing tomorrow?

33:41.323 --> 33:43.760
We could go around the island
a couple times with it.

33:44.848 --> 33:46.850
I have to go to
Simone's birthday.

33:47.286 --> 33:49.505
The party can't go on all day.

33:55.250 --> 33:56.643
Simone, cool it.

33:58.645 --> 34:00.299
When you're not looking,

34:00.342 --> 34:01.778
I'm gonna get you.

34:04.259 --> 34:05.434
[grunt]

34:12.093 --> 34:14.226
I don't want any trouble
in my store, Mitzi.

34:14.269 --> 34:15.444
What, I wasn't-

34:19.709 --> 34:22.451
Wow, she really punched you.

34:22.495 --> 34:23.844
She's crazy.

34:23.887 --> 34:25.672
Is she always like that?
-Yeah.

34:25.715 --> 34:27.717
Hey you two,
get back here.

34:30.285 --> 34:32.679
[snowmobile revving]

34:32.722 --> 34:35.943
STORE OWNER:
Is this the TV station?

34:35.986 --> 34:38.989
Yes, I'd like to report those
two girls that are stealing.

34:41.731 --> 34:45.735
Blessed are the meek for they
shall inherit the Earth.

34:48.521 --> 34:49.739
[sighs]

34:53.482 --> 34:56.268
[rumbling spiritual
flute chords]

34:56.311 --> 34:57.486
[laughing]

35:01.577 --> 35:03.101
Huh?

35:03.144 --> 35:04.580
[gasps]

35:04.624 --> 35:06.974
I haven't been out here
since Halley's Comet.

35:07.017 --> 35:08.976
ANNABELLE:
Yes, he has.

35:09.019 --> 35:10.673
He was in a deep
sleep last time.

35:10.717 --> 35:11.761
[Mitzi giggles]

35:11.805 --> 35:13.720
Hope was having
lugubrious century.

35:15.548 --> 35:17.898
WILLIAM:
I love it out here.

35:17.941 --> 35:19.334
It's so peaceful.

35:20.727 --> 35:22.990
Dark and quiet.

35:23.033 --> 35:24.644
When traveling through space,

35:24.687 --> 35:28.648
one must always remember to
follow the rules of the galaxy.

35:28.691 --> 35:30.171
There's only one
rule I remember.

35:31.433 --> 35:33.479
I learned that on Venus.

35:33.522 --> 35:35.785
Leave earth on earth.

35:37.222 --> 35:40.181
Look how beautiful
Mother Earth is.

35:44.707 --> 35:46.535
She's dying.

35:48.537 --> 35:49.973
I love her so much.

35:52.062 --> 35:54.761
[sombre spiritual
rattling instrumental]

35:54.804 --> 35:58.808
[sombre spiritual humming]

36:10.820 --> 36:14.824
♪ music continues

36:46.682 --> 36:48.206
Hm.

36:48.249 --> 36:50.251
It looks better than it did.

37:02.785 --> 37:04.396
[chuckling] Is
that a love bite?

37:04.439 --> 37:07.268
More like a love punch
without the love.

37:07.877 --> 37:09.401
Simone?

37:09.444 --> 37:10.663
Yeah.

37:10.793 --> 37:12.578
The Muskrats are bullies.

37:12.621 --> 37:13.840
[clear throats and hork]

37:18.323 --> 37:19.672
And disruptors.

37:20.977 --> 37:22.283
Yeah.

37:22.327 --> 37:24.111
I was always afraid of them.

37:24.154 --> 37:27.201
How can so much badness
come from one family?

37:27.245 --> 37:28.289
They were born that way.

37:28.333 --> 37:30.204
CHARLIE B:
Yeah, they're rotten.

37:31.074 --> 37:33.512
So are you going to quit
talking to Honeyboy?

37:33.555 --> 37:34.817
Na ah.

37:37.342 --> 37:41.302
[slurping]

37:41.346 --> 37:42.564
[in unison] Ah.

37:48.483 --> 37:50.485
You ever hear from
that city guy?

37:51.312 --> 37:52.487
Nope.

37:56.056 --> 37:59.059
[slurping]

38:00.365 --> 38:02.018
[in unison] Ah.

38:08.329 --> 38:10.418
So you and Honeyboy
gonna get it on?

38:14.901 --> 38:16.685
Okay, Charlie,

38:16.729 --> 38:18.296
leave her alone.

38:21.124 --> 38:22.735
MITZI:
Almost got it. One more heave.

38:22.778 --> 38:23.997
I can't do it.

38:24.040 --> 38:25.651
[grunting]

38:25.694 --> 38:28.697
You know Charlie can't
do this kind of lifting.

38:35.922 --> 38:39.752
You could've joined the army
and gotten some real muscle.

38:45.540 --> 38:47.934
Maybe you heard millinery
instead of military.

38:47.977 --> 38:51.503
Go, go design a hat that we
can use as a tiny hotel room.

38:51.546 --> 38:52.504
[chuckling]

38:52.547 --> 38:54.375
Who buys hats
anymore anyways?

38:54.419 --> 38:56.377
I'm gonna design one
and name it after you.

38:56.421 --> 38:58.031
The Annabelle.

38:58.074 --> 39:01.600
I don't want no damn
hat with my name on it.

39:01.643 --> 39:03.906
Where's William?

39:03.950 --> 39:05.778
He gets me out of the
house no problem.

39:07.954 --> 39:08.955
[laughing]

39:08.998 --> 39:10.739
Where are you
taking me anyways?

39:10.783 --> 39:12.350
Somewhere nice, Auntie.

39:14.439 --> 39:15.657
[soft instrumental]

39:15.701 --> 39:17.137
MITZI:
Are you doing one
of your plays?

39:17.180 --> 39:18.530
CHARLIE B: Yep.

39:18.573 --> 39:21.576
I'm sure it's going
to be very beautiful.

39:24.449 --> 39:26.320
Mitzi always helps.

39:30.498 --> 39:32.370
She's designing the costumes.

39:39.464 --> 39:40.639
Yes.

39:40.682 --> 39:42.423
I'll help you.

39:42.467 --> 39:46.471
[soft instrumental]

39:48.473 --> 39:50.475
♪ music continues

40:09.450 --> 40:10.930
How's your eye?

40:10.973 --> 40:12.627
Didn't see it coming.

40:12.671 --> 40:14.499
Next time I'll be ready.

40:16.022 --> 40:18.111
Why Simone Muskrat?

40:18.154 --> 40:19.329
[clears throat and horks]

40:20.418 --> 40:22.985
That desperate for
female attention?

40:23.029 --> 40:24.465
No.

40:24.509 --> 40:25.858
I like being alone.

40:26.424 --> 40:28.426
Tell her to buzz off.

40:34.867 --> 40:36.346
I'm terrible with makeup.

40:36.695 --> 40:38.044
Last time you made
us look like monsters

40:38.087 --> 40:40.481
and you weren't even trying.

40:40.525 --> 40:41.656
Right.

40:42.440 --> 40:44.833
Well now we know
your special talent.

40:44.877 --> 40:46.792
You can show these gals
how to walk like zombies.

40:46.835 --> 40:48.663
Ah, there we go, okay.

40:49.838 --> 40:52.624
Grrrrr.

40:52.667 --> 40:54.060
Come on, try it.

40:56.279 --> 41:01.154
Grrrrr.

41:01.197 --> 41:05.071
[upbeat country music]

41:11.077 --> 41:14.515
♪ Love is

41:14.559 --> 41:18.998
♪ A warm spring break

41:19.041 --> 41:21.348
♪ It fills the soul

41:21.391 --> 41:24.830
♪ Time and again

41:24.873 --> 41:27.659
♪ When you think it's gone

41:27.702 --> 41:31.184
♪ That it's gone for good

41:31.227 --> 41:34.579
♪ It reappears like magic

41:34.622 --> 41:37.625
♪ Baby, like it should

41:39.801 --> 41:42.543
♪ Love is patient

41:42.587 --> 41:45.546
♪ Love is kind

41:45.590 --> 41:49.071
♪ And when it
finds you it will ♪

41:49.115 --> 41:52.901
♪ Blow your mind

41:52.945 --> 41:54.773
[whistling]

41:55.469 --> 41:56.905
Whatcha doing?

41:58.646 --> 42:01.649
Finishing headdresses
for Charlie B's play.

42:03.564 --> 42:05.566
Summer's flown by.

42:05.610 --> 42:08.308
And I can't believe I got
sucked into doing this.

42:08.351 --> 42:09.744
I got mail for you.

42:22.452 --> 42:24.411
So, what do you think?

42:24.454 --> 42:26.500
It looks good to me.

42:26.544 --> 42:28.720
Who's Ringo Leaves-No-Shadow?

42:28.763 --> 42:30.373
Some guy I used to know.

43:00.316 --> 43:02.318
We look like an Incan God.

43:03.232 --> 43:04.799
We are royal.

43:07.802 --> 43:10.109
You are the strangest
person I know.

43:10.152 --> 43:11.763
When did that happen?

43:11.806 --> 43:13.416
As soon as I got here.

43:15.810 --> 43:17.203
And everything changed.

43:21.424 --> 43:23.513
I had plans to go
to hat school.

43:23.557 --> 43:25.559
I still want to
but who knows?

43:26.691 --> 43:28.475
I could teach you how to
make whistles out of these.

43:28.518 --> 43:30.651
We use them around here,
it's a night thing.

43:30.695 --> 43:32.218
Yeah, I remember.

43:35.221 --> 43:36.657
So what do you do here,

43:36.701 --> 43:38.137
besides drive your dad's boat?

43:38.180 --> 43:40.313
Hunt, fish,

43:40.356 --> 43:42.228
get drunk, hang out.

43:42.271 --> 43:43.708
What do you really wanna do?

43:43.751 --> 43:45.666
I don't know.

43:45.710 --> 43:46.841
Get my own boat,

43:46.885 --> 43:47.842
build a house,

43:47.886 --> 43:48.974
have kids.

43:49.017 --> 43:51.019
I wanted to make things.

43:51.454 --> 43:53.065
Be on a runway in Paris.

43:54.066 --> 43:56.851
Live the fast life
at a turtle's pace.

43:57.852 --> 43:59.637
Learn three languages.

43:59.680 --> 44:00.812
Meet the Dalai Lama.

44:00.855 --> 44:02.509
You want to meet a llama?

44:03.858 --> 44:05.686
Yeah, something like that.

44:13.563 --> 44:15.174
Shoot.

44:15.217 --> 44:17.045
I'm almost out of sticks.

44:17.916 --> 44:19.134
Let's get more.

44:20.440 --> 44:21.876
Do you have time?

44:22.877 --> 44:24.183
I'm my own boss.

44:24.226 --> 44:25.880
I have a couple hours.

44:26.272 --> 44:28.840
[uplifting music]

44:28.883 --> 44:30.450
Hopefully we'll
find more sticks.

44:30.493 --> 44:32.017
It looks like
we're running low.

44:32.060 --> 44:33.627
[chuckles] I'm telling you.

44:33.671 --> 44:35.107
This giant pile's here.
-You can never have enough.

44:35.150 --> 44:36.456
Come on, keep it going.

44:36.499 --> 44:37.979
I haven't worked out yet today.
-All right. Okay.

44:38.023 --> 44:41.026
There's one on, one
more I got my eye on.

44:44.246 --> 44:45.857
Let me know if it's too much.

44:45.900 --> 44:47.728
Whoa, gonna be too much.

44:47.772 --> 44:48.990
Wah!

44:49.121 --> 44:50.731
Don't laugh at me .

44:50.775 --> 44:51.863
Okay, come on.

44:51.906 --> 44:52.864
HONEYBOY: No.

44:52.907 --> 44:54.561
[laughing]

44:54.604 --> 44:58.608
[gentle instrumental]

45:00.610 --> 45:04.614
♪ music continues

45:13.536 --> 45:14.755
Here.

45:20.456 --> 45:23.068
I always thought you would fall
for one of those macho guys.

45:23.111 --> 45:24.460
Me, too.

45:24.504 --> 45:26.332
I mean, I have.

45:27.507 --> 45:30.423
[laughing] What?

45:30.466 --> 45:31.816
Shut up.

45:32.120 --> 45:34.253
Things never change.

45:34.296 --> 45:36.298
It's the same as
when we were kids.

45:36.342 --> 45:38.344
It was boring then,
and it's boring now.

45:39.519 --> 45:41.347
I miss this quiet place.

45:42.391 --> 45:44.785
There's no industrial sounds.

45:44.829 --> 45:46.656
I want to get old here.

45:46.787 --> 45:48.615
Don't you miss the fun stuff?

45:48.658 --> 45:50.660
All my fun stuff's up here.

45:52.575 --> 45:54.186
Can take that anywhere.

45:56.362 --> 45:58.364
My fun stuff is
in other places.

46:02.498 --> 46:04.849
What about teachers' college?

46:04.892 --> 46:06.154
I'll get there.

46:07.677 --> 46:08.853
Sometime.

46:21.343 --> 46:24.956
TV ANNOUNCER:
And now for Owl Island News
where we give a hoot.

46:24.999 --> 46:26.566
[owl hooting]

46:26.609 --> 46:30.483
There have been a number of
incidence involving two girls.

46:30.526 --> 46:35.488
They are breaking into houses
and stealing from homes.

46:35.531 --> 46:39.840
Stop before you get
into real trouble!

46:39.884 --> 46:42.887
TV ANNOUNCER:
And now, back to your
scheduled program.

46:43.888 --> 46:47.152
TV CHEF:
We're going to take this
beautiful moose tongue

46:47.195 --> 46:49.850
and fry it with onions,
salt and some vegetables.

46:49.894 --> 46:51.591
Is that moose tongue?

46:52.374 --> 46:54.028
It's gross.

46:55.290 --> 46:56.988
It's a local cook.

46:57.031 --> 47:00.034
I think they were even on
that show "Master Chief".

47:03.211 --> 47:05.039
TV CHEF:
So brown up all the sides.

47:10.610 --> 47:12.699
That shouldn't take long
and then we'll move on

47:12.742 --> 47:14.396
to this side dish here.

47:17.312 --> 47:19.575
[coughing]

47:20.446 --> 47:25.407
[labored breathing]

47:25.451 --> 47:26.887
I feel like crap.

47:30.456 --> 47:31.631
Charlie?

47:31.674 --> 47:33.415
Charlie?

47:33.459 --> 47:34.416
Charlie?

47:34.460 --> 47:36.070
Call Honeyboy right now!

47:38.464 --> 47:39.682
Charlie.

47:39.726 --> 47:41.728
MITZI:
Honeyboy, I need
you right now.

47:46.428 --> 47:50.432
[sirens echoing]

48:05.099 --> 48:09.625
[ominous music]

48:09.669 --> 48:12.150
[owl hooting]

48:17.285 --> 48:21.420
[thundering]
[spiritual music]

48:25.293 --> 48:29.123
♪ continues

48:31.952 --> 48:33.954
SIMONE:
Mitzi Bearclaw.

48:37.305 --> 48:38.524
[growling]

48:41.788 --> 48:43.094
Muskrats.

48:43.137 --> 48:44.312
[clears throat and horks]

48:44.530 --> 48:47.489
[demonic voice] We
are not the Muskrats.

48:47.533 --> 48:50.144
SIMONE:
Mitzi Bearclaw.

48:50.188 --> 48:51.624
You're so weak.

48:51.667 --> 48:52.842
Don't touch me!

48:54.018 --> 48:55.062
[laughing]

48:55.106 --> 48:56.977
What's this?

48:57.021 --> 48:58.848
Just as I thought.

49:00.328 --> 49:01.547
It burns.

49:04.985 --> 49:06.334
Why did you do that?

49:06.378 --> 49:07.596
It's nothing.

49:08.249 --> 49:10.730
It will decay very soon.

49:10.773 --> 49:13.167
These are worth fighting for.

49:13.211 --> 49:15.126
Have some.
[laughing]

49:15.169 --> 49:17.128
Let's give her the
full treatment.

49:17.171 --> 49:19.478
Her simple life has
made her simple.

49:19.521 --> 49:21.480
We surprise attack at dawn

49:21.523 --> 49:23.308
from the rear.

49:23.351 --> 49:24.526
This is the best.

49:25.832 --> 49:27.312
Dinosaur blood.

49:27.355 --> 49:28.791
Black gold.

49:29.618 --> 49:31.011
Texas tea.

49:32.752 --> 49:37.365
[laughing]
[Mitzi screaming]

49:37.409 --> 49:38.627
Stop!

49:39.715 --> 49:43.719
[thunderous instrumental]

49:48.724 --> 49:52.206
♪ continues

49:56.080 --> 49:58.517
WILLIAM:
Hit it hard, Mitzi.

49:58.560 --> 50:00.910
Hit it so you will
make the trees shake.

50:00.954 --> 50:04.566
You will make the dogs bark.

50:04.610 --> 50:06.264
The rocks will come
out of the water

50:06.307 --> 50:09.354
and smash these guys!

50:09.397 --> 50:14.359
[rhythmic thunderous drums]

50:14.402 --> 50:15.708
You gotta run.

50:15.751 --> 50:17.188
Run, run!

50:17.231 --> 50:19.625
[rhythmic thunderous drums]

50:19.668 --> 50:21.540
Run!

50:21.583 --> 50:24.543
[rhythmic thunderous drums]

50:24.586 --> 50:26.936
[screaming]

50:40.167 --> 50:43.170
[crackling]

50:46.130 --> 50:51.004
[knife whittling]

50:59.926 --> 51:04.278
[soft spiritual
flute instrumental]

51:13.287 --> 51:16.290
♪ continues

51:33.307 --> 51:37.485
[eerie instrumental]

51:40.488 --> 51:44.971
[laughing]

51:45.014 --> 51:48.017
MITZI:
Mary and Moe had a
lot of fun doing that.

51:50.324 --> 51:52.500
I think I'll write
something for them.

51:52.544 --> 51:54.285
A love story maybe.

51:54.328 --> 51:57.157
It'll take place in
the Bush or a boat.

51:57.201 --> 51:59.028
Better yet, a canoe.

52:01.944 --> 52:04.947
[coughing]

52:14.174 --> 52:15.741
[knocking]

52:17.134 --> 52:18.352
Come in, preacher.

52:18.396 --> 52:20.180
Come in.
-Anni, William.

52:20.224 --> 52:21.834
It was nice to
receive your call.

52:21.877 --> 52:23.314
I haven't seen
you in a while.

52:23.357 --> 52:24.619
Anni, Charlie B.

52:24.663 --> 52:26.055
Hey.

52:26.186 --> 52:27.709
PREACHER:
How is Annabelle?

52:27.753 --> 52:29.363
It was good to see
her out and about.

52:29.407 --> 52:32.410
Oh, having Mitzi and Charlie
home has been a godsend.

52:34.063 --> 52:36.065
It's good to see
you again, Mitzi.

52:36.109 --> 52:37.502
It's, uh,

52:37.545 --> 52:39.243
nice to see you working
with the young people here.

52:39.286 --> 52:40.722
Yeah that was fun.

52:41.767 --> 52:44.117
PREACHER:
It's good to have
the youth around.

52:44.161 --> 52:46.728
It breathes new life
into old Owl Island.

52:46.772 --> 52:48.121
It gives us hope.

52:48.165 --> 52:51.168
Do you think Annabelle
would mind a little prayer?

52:51.429 --> 52:54.214
Prayer is always
appreciated, preacher.

52:54.258 --> 52:55.737
Meegwetch for coming.

52:57.391 --> 52:59.350
ANNABELLE:
Anni, preacher.

52:59.393 --> 53:00.612
PREACHER:
Anni, Annabelle.

53:02.962 --> 53:04.529
How are you this evening?

53:04.572 --> 53:05.965
ANNABELLE: I couldn't be better, Minister.

53:06.008 --> 53:07.358
WILLIAM:
Where are you off to?

53:07.401 --> 53:08.924
A friend's.

53:08.968 --> 53:11.884
ANNABELLE:
Mitzi is joining in
and not as uppity

53:11.927 --> 53:15.104
as she once was when
she first arrived.

53:15.148 --> 53:19.152
[soft classical music]

53:25.158 --> 53:29.162
♪ music continues

53:30.511 --> 53:32.339
[door slamming]

53:35.299 --> 53:36.517
[howling]

53:48.268 --> 53:50.227
HONEYBOY:
You look nice.

53:50.270 --> 53:52.229
MITZI:
Thanks.

53:52.272 --> 53:54.622
I thought I should
keep up my profile.

53:54.666 --> 53:56.015
I'm gonna be a fashion expert

53:56.058 --> 53:58.235
sometime in the near future,
you know?

53:58.278 --> 53:59.540
Huh?

54:00.498 --> 54:02.456
You think you'll
ever leave here?

54:10.377 --> 54:13.380
When my granddad,
Oliver, passes away,

54:14.990 --> 54:17.993
I'm going to be Owl Island's
medicine man.

54:18.733 --> 54:20.344
I'm trained that way.

54:21.519 --> 54:22.781
So, no.

54:22.824 --> 54:24.217
This is my life.

54:27.873 --> 54:30.876
You think you could see
yourself staying here?

54:33.487 --> 54:36.490
March, April, six months.

54:38.492 --> 54:40.189
So far so good.

54:41.408 --> 54:43.280
I don't miss my cell phone.

54:44.063 --> 54:45.717
All the calls I used to get.

54:45.760 --> 54:47.588
You wouldn't believe it.

54:48.850 --> 54:50.287
Who used to call?

54:51.375 --> 54:53.638
Fashion design houses,

54:53.681 --> 54:56.336
models who needed
a designer hat.

54:56.380 --> 54:58.338
You name it, they called.

55:02.037 --> 55:03.691
I'm just pulling your leg.

55:03.735 --> 55:05.345
No one called.

55:05.389 --> 55:06.781
I just waited for calls.

55:08.392 --> 55:10.350
I can wait for calls anywhere.

55:13.701 --> 55:15.137
Wait here with me.

55:18.924 --> 55:19.881
[laughing]

55:19.925 --> 55:21.927
Hey, Dad, what do you think?

55:23.581 --> 55:26.497
Uncle Oliver here
looks like a war hero.

55:26.540 --> 55:28.150
Well I still got it in me.

55:28.760 --> 55:30.718
It looks pretty good, I bet.

55:31.632 --> 55:33.504
Yeah, I'm going to
wear that for the next

55:33.547 --> 55:35.549
Veteran's Day parade.

55:38.291 --> 55:39.727
When'd you learn to do this?

55:39.901 --> 55:41.903
She cut two stacks
of wood today.

55:42.600 --> 55:45.559
That's the kind of
woman we need around here.

55:45.603 --> 55:46.778
Where's Charlie?

55:46.821 --> 55:48.083
Lying down.

55:48.823 --> 55:50.259
I'll save him some fish.

55:51.565 --> 55:53.567
I'll save some for
the preacher, too.

55:54.742 --> 55:55.874
I'll be working in my room,

55:55.917 --> 55:58.746
I don't want to
disturb your fish fry.

56:00.313 --> 56:03.316
UNCLE OLIVER:
It's got external
uses too, you know.

56:03.447 --> 56:07.538
WILLIAM:
Yeah it's good for
your aging legs.

56:07.581 --> 56:08.930
[William chuckling]

56:08.974 --> 56:12.412
UNCLE OLIVER:
Remember that.
Bannock medicine.

56:12.456 --> 56:14.153
WILLIAM:
Pull up a chair, preacher.

56:14.849 --> 56:18.766
UNCLE OLIVER:
You want some Saturday night
bannock to go with that fish?

56:18.810 --> 56:20.942
PREACHER:
Thank you, but no, Oliver.

56:20.986 --> 56:22.553
I've been dry for
six years now.

56:22.596 --> 56:25.904
Praise the Lord.
Meegwetch to the Creator.

56:25.947 --> 56:28.385
William, you should come
to my parish sometime.

56:29.342 --> 56:30.996
We have groups that
pray together.

56:31.039 --> 56:32.606
It's pretty wonderful.

56:32.650 --> 56:37.481
[soft country music]

56:37.524 --> 56:41.615
[soft snoring]

56:42.616 --> 56:44.226
MITZI:
Dad, Dad.

56:47.404 --> 56:48.970
It's time to go to bed.

56:50.058 --> 56:51.625
Come.

56:52.452 --> 56:53.801
Come on.

56:54.802 --> 56:59.241
[soft country music]

57:01.243 --> 57:06.205
♪ Bringing out light
the fire we know ♪

57:07.641 --> 57:12.429
♪ Oh, at the end of the song

57:16.650 --> 57:21.438
♪ Is the hardest of goodbyes

57:24.658 --> 57:29.446
♪ Are the ones we cry

57:33.014 --> 57:37.802
♪ Someday you'll
understand, oh ♪

57:39.020 --> 57:43.024
♪ The reasons I must fly

57:49.509 --> 57:51.946
PREACHER:
In the Book of Isaiah.

57:51.990 --> 57:54.993
The great prophet
states that the Creator

57:55.036 --> 57:57.212
will not grow tired or weary,

57:57.256 --> 58:00.259
and his deep understanding,
no one can fathom.

58:01.303 --> 58:05.046
He gives strength to the
weary and increases the power

58:05.090 --> 58:06.657
of the weak.

58:06.700 --> 58:09.094
Even the youth grow
tired and weary.

58:10.487 --> 58:15.404
Young men and women
will stumble and fall,

58:15.448 --> 58:17.755
but those who
hope in the Lord

58:17.798 --> 58:19.539
will renew their strength.

58:19.583 --> 58:22.455
They will soar on
wings like eagles.

58:22.499 --> 58:24.022
They will run and
not grow weary.

58:24.065 --> 58:27.547
They will walk
and not be faint.

58:27.591 --> 58:30.071
We give thanks to
the grandfathers.

58:30.115 --> 58:35.076
The sun, the rain,
the stars overhead,

58:35.120 --> 58:37.775
and the Earth
beneath our feet.

58:37.818 --> 58:41.822
[soft country music]

58:43.824 --> 58:46.871
♪ music continues

58:46.914 --> 58:51.223
We thank the Creator for
looking after our loved ones

58:51.266 --> 58:53.747
as they continue
on their journey

58:53.791 --> 58:56.620
back to the spirit world.

58:56.663 --> 58:58.578
[soft country music]

58:58.622 --> 59:02.582
♪ You know the kind

59:06.760 --> 59:10.764
♪ Things that I always
meant to say before today ♪

59:20.600 --> 59:21.732
I missed you yesterday.

59:21.775 --> 59:23.211
I was there.

59:24.212 --> 59:26.084
So was Simone.

59:26.606 --> 59:28.303
I don't even know
who was there.

59:28.347 --> 59:31.089
I'm sorry to hear
about your grandpa.

59:31.132 --> 59:33.526
It was a sad day
for everyone.

59:33.570 --> 59:35.310
I can't talk about it.

59:36.050 --> 59:37.574
I can't even believe it.

59:37.617 --> 59:39.576
Why does she cling
to you like a leach?

59:39.619 --> 59:41.621
She's got nothing
better to do.

59:43.623 --> 59:45.582
I don't know what
I'm doing here.

59:45.625 --> 59:47.453
One of the first things
I said to you was,

59:47.496 --> 59:49.150
"Life here is short."

59:53.677 --> 59:54.591
What?

59:54.634 --> 59:55.809
Wait.

59:57.811 --> 59:59.770
I don't want this
to be all there is.

59:59.813 --> 1:00:02.207
There's a whole wide
world out there.

1:00:06.254 --> 1:00:07.516
Yeah.

1:00:08.169 --> 1:00:09.344
I know.

1:00:11.433 --> 1:00:13.435
Wait, I'm not saying I-

1:00:14.828 --> 1:00:16.395
I still want us to be-

1:00:16.438 --> 1:00:17.701
Honeyboy?

1:00:17.744 --> 1:00:20.399
[motor rumbling]

1:00:20.442 --> 1:00:24.838
[crying]

1:00:36.937 --> 1:00:38.417
[knocking]

1:00:42.769 --> 1:00:44.031
Ringo.

1:00:44.379 --> 1:00:45.554
Mitzi?

1:00:46.033 --> 1:00:47.208
Hi.

1:00:48.775 --> 1:00:50.342
Hi.

1:00:50.385 --> 1:00:52.213
MITZI:
Ah, what are you doing here?

1:00:53.388 --> 1:00:55.477
[crying]

1:01:00.395 --> 1:01:01.614
Dad?

1:01:02.876 --> 1:01:05.705
This is Ringo Leaves-No-Shadow.

1:01:05.749 --> 1:01:09.578
[crying]

1:01:11.929 --> 1:01:13.974
RINGO:
I wish I had come earlier.

1:01:14.018 --> 1:01:15.933
It's different
than I expected.

1:01:15.976 --> 1:01:17.412
It's so empty.

1:01:18.892 --> 1:01:20.285
I used to think that too.

1:01:21.808 --> 1:01:24.681
What's the future for people
who live on an island this-

1:01:26.073 --> 1:01:27.248
poor?

1:01:28.902 --> 1:01:30.295
So far from everything.

1:01:31.122 --> 1:01:32.689
So I guess you're not staying.

1:01:34.342 --> 1:01:35.909
I'm thinking of
moving back home.

1:01:35.953 --> 1:01:37.955
I've been offered a
job at the casino.

1:01:39.347 --> 1:01:40.740
And your thesis?

1:01:41.132 --> 1:01:42.742
I got tired of academia.

1:01:43.612 --> 1:01:45.179
I'm going to take a rest.

1:01:45.789 --> 1:01:47.138
And besides,

1:01:47.181 --> 1:01:50.184
I could do that
anytime, anywhere.

1:01:54.580 --> 1:01:56.060
MITZI:
What's this?

1:01:56.103 --> 1:01:57.583
RINGO:
Your portfolio.

1:01:57.626 --> 1:01:59.628
It was just sitting there and-

1:02:01.195 --> 1:02:03.763
You're good, Mitzi.

1:02:03.807 --> 1:02:05.112
You should really-

1:02:05.156 --> 1:02:07.158
I'm needed more here
than I thought.

1:02:08.507 --> 1:02:09.769
My parents-

1:02:09.813 --> 1:02:12.772
My parents would
never live like this.

1:02:15.819 --> 1:02:19.779
All of your thesis work has
really overtaken your brain.

1:02:19.823 --> 1:02:21.476
Do you hear yourself?

1:02:22.347 --> 1:02:24.697
You sound like those
textbooks you study.

1:02:24.741 --> 1:02:26.568
You're a cyborg Indian.

1:02:32.836 --> 1:02:35.664
[dog barking]

1:02:35.708 --> 1:02:37.710
RINGO:
Things never turn out the
way I thought they would.

1:02:37.754 --> 1:02:39.146
How so?

1:02:40.017 --> 1:02:41.975
I thought you'd be
leaving with me.

1:02:43.020 --> 1:02:45.109
It crossed my mind a
couple months ago but-

1:02:45.152 --> 1:02:46.327
who knows?

1:02:46.371 --> 1:02:49.287
[quirky jazz music]

1:02:49.330 --> 1:02:50.549
Who's that?

1:02:51.855 --> 1:02:53.595
Simone Ratface?

1:02:56.860 --> 1:02:58.557
I'm Simone Muskrat.

1:02:59.297 --> 1:03:01.821
Ringo Leaves-No-Shadow.

1:03:01.865 --> 1:03:04.824
SIMONE:
I'm so sorry if your time
spent here was boring.

1:03:04.868 --> 1:03:07.827
It wasn't so boring
for Beary over there.

1:03:07.871 --> 1:03:09.742
She had her claws
in everything.

1:03:09.786 --> 1:03:11.396
If you need a
name of a victim-

1:03:11.439 --> 1:03:12.701
No.

1:03:13.615 --> 1:03:15.008
Wasn't boring at all.

1:03:15.922 --> 1:03:20.361
Let's go, Simone.
This is none of your business.

1:03:20.405 --> 1:03:23.974
Mitzi was sleeping with
my boyfriend, Honeyboy.

1:03:24.017 --> 1:03:26.063
They thought I didn't know.

1:03:26.106 --> 1:03:27.325
What?

1:03:27.368 --> 1:03:28.500
She's a liar.

1:03:28.543 --> 1:03:30.110
I'm not your boyfriend.

1:03:32.460 --> 1:03:35.246
I knew something was going on.

1:03:35.289 --> 1:03:39.293
He was way too happy
and always whistling.

1:03:42.035 --> 1:03:43.210
Okay.

1:03:44.298 --> 1:03:45.865
I get it.

1:03:45.909 --> 1:03:47.388
It all makes sense.

1:03:48.085 --> 1:03:50.174
I thought I was
doing you a favor .

1:03:50.217 --> 1:03:52.524
Giving you some hope
for the future,

1:03:52.567 --> 1:03:55.570
offering you a
place in my life.

1:04:03.317 --> 1:04:04.884
SIMONE:
H-Boy.

1:04:06.451 --> 1:04:08.583
I'll leave your
boat at the marina.

1:04:08.627 --> 1:04:10.194
Just get it there.

1:04:10.237 --> 1:04:14.241
[quirky jazz instrumental]

1:04:16.243 --> 1:04:17.854
♪ music continues

1:04:17.897 --> 1:04:19.246
MITZI:
What just happened?

1:04:19.290 --> 1:04:21.292
HONEYBOY:
Simone just stole my boat.

1:04:22.423 --> 1:04:24.643
And Ringo Leaves-No-Shadow.

1:04:24.686 --> 1:04:25.905
[horn blowing]

1:04:30.605 --> 1:04:34.609
[rhythmic singing
and drumming]

1:04:43.618 --> 1:04:47.622
♪ music continues

1:05:10.645 --> 1:05:14.911
[traditional indigenous singing]

1:05:23.658 --> 1:05:26.661
♪ music continues

1:05:39.979 --> 1:05:41.372
CHARLIE B:
Whatcha making?

1:05:42.982 --> 1:05:44.505
Ah, I don't know.

1:05:44.984 --> 1:05:48.509
I never understood what's
with you and hats.

1:05:48.553 --> 1:05:50.120
It's not dresses,

1:05:50.163 --> 1:05:52.992
not shoes, pants, Spanx.

1:05:54.951 --> 1:05:56.169
But hats.

1:05:56.561 --> 1:05:58.650
Hats hold a mystery for me.

1:05:58.693 --> 1:06:00.130
They're a symbol of power,

1:06:00.173 --> 1:06:04.047
but a source of
strength and a comfort.

1:06:04.090 --> 1:06:06.353
A part of a uniform but off.

1:06:06.397 --> 1:06:08.529
You wear the right one,

1:06:08.573 --> 1:06:10.009
mind-probing headgear.

1:06:11.880 --> 1:06:14.666
Making protection,
warmth and in a way,

1:06:14.709 --> 1:06:16.929
self-identification.

1:06:16.973 --> 1:06:18.800
God, listen to me.

1:06:19.279 --> 1:06:22.587
I think I could win wars
with a perfectly designed

1:06:22.630 --> 1:06:24.458
aerodynamic cap.

1:06:25.111 --> 1:06:28.158
You could go into
any danger zone

1:06:28.201 --> 1:06:29.420
and go unnoticed

1:06:29.463 --> 1:06:30.551
and noticed when
you want to be.

1:06:30.595 --> 1:06:33.424
I mean, come on,
need I say more?

1:06:35.382 --> 1:06:36.818
Well, the passion's real.

1:06:40.735 --> 1:06:42.346
We are passionate people,

1:06:42.389 --> 1:06:43.869
you and me.

1:06:43.912 --> 1:06:45.305
You and I.

1:06:51.833 --> 1:06:53.226
[sighs] You and I.

1:06:58.101 --> 1:07:02.801
We belong to a near extinct
tribe of thing makers.

1:07:02.844 --> 1:07:07.588
[soft spiritual
flute instrumental]

1:07:07.632 --> 1:07:10.417
You make hats, Mitzi.

1:07:10.461 --> 1:07:12.941
The world can never
have enough chapeaus.

1:07:14.160 --> 1:07:16.597
Especially the ones
that give you power.

1:07:18.599 --> 1:07:20.993
And you, Charlie B.

1:07:24.257 --> 1:07:25.476
Not sure.

1:07:29.132 --> 1:07:31.090
I don't think I'm going
to teachers' college.

1:07:35.660 --> 1:07:38.271
You have to be the one
to travel the cosmos.

1:07:47.106 --> 1:07:49.413
ANNABELLE:
I need to go to the bathroom!

1:07:49.456 --> 1:07:50.675
Mitzi.

1:07:51.980 --> 1:07:53.112
William.

1:07:54.287 --> 1:07:56.637
Where the hell is everybody?

1:08:00.511 --> 1:08:05.211
[background chatter]

1:08:06.647 --> 1:08:07.866
[Mitzi clears throat]

1:08:08.867 --> 1:08:10.129
Sorry we're late.

1:08:10.173 --> 1:08:11.522
My mom wanted to come.

1:08:13.176 --> 1:08:15.178
Okay, so we're trying
to do something surreal

1:08:15.221 --> 1:08:16.440
with this performance.

1:08:16.483 --> 1:08:17.789
What's that?

1:08:17.832 --> 1:08:19.878
It's like a dream.

1:08:19.921 --> 1:08:21.967
A strange one but
it's really happening.

1:08:22.010 --> 1:08:23.795
That happens to
me all the time.

1:08:23.838 --> 1:08:25.971
Like the time we're
sitting in the park

1:08:26.014 --> 1:08:28.147
and a stray dog came
by and frenched you.

1:08:28.191 --> 1:08:29.409
[giggles]

1:08:29.453 --> 1:08:31.281
I told you to never
talk about that again.

1:08:31.324 --> 1:08:33.761
CHARLIE B:
I can think of worse things
than being kissed by a dog.

1:08:34.545 --> 1:08:38.114
Now I know we were supposed
to do this months ago

1:08:38.157 --> 1:08:39.680
but I want to thank you
all for holding tight

1:08:39.724 --> 1:08:41.291
and standing by.

1:08:41.334 --> 1:08:43.336
That's what we
Owl Islanders do.

1:08:44.120 --> 1:08:46.818
Tonight we stage our
performance for the community

1:08:46.861 --> 1:08:49.908
and for me to experience
this with all of you

1:08:49.951 --> 1:08:52.954
it'll be like a dream,
but a real one.

1:08:53.781 --> 1:08:55.305
Any questions?

1:08:55.348 --> 1:08:57.133
Why do they call
you Charlie B?

1:08:57.176 --> 1:09:00.310
Mostly to pay tribute to
everything that I love.

1:09:00.353 --> 1:09:02.747
Ah, the written word,
its authors,

1:09:02.790 --> 1:09:04.227
uh, Charles Baudelaire,

1:09:04.270 --> 1:09:05.402
Charles Bukowski,

1:09:05.445 --> 1:09:06.925
Charlotte Bronte.

1:09:06.968 --> 1:09:10.711
You know, the B unites us
in my most humble way.

1:09:14.367 --> 1:09:15.673
[gasps]

1:09:15.716 --> 1:09:16.935
MAN:
Somebody get him a chair.

1:09:26.379 --> 1:09:29.382
[quirky jazz instrumental]

1:09:34.387 --> 1:09:38.522
♪ music continues

1:09:38.565 --> 1:09:40.959
[grunting]

1:09:41.002 --> 1:09:42.352
What are you doing?

1:09:42.395 --> 1:09:43.744
[rumbling]
[sizzling]

1:09:43.788 --> 1:09:46.182
[distant screeching]
[quirky jazz instrumental]

1:09:46.225 --> 1:09:47.400
Where did you come from?

1:09:47.444 --> 1:09:49.272
I wouldn't miss
this for the world.

1:09:49.315 --> 1:09:53.319
[quirky jazz instrumental]

1:09:55.321 --> 1:09:56.757
♪ music continues

1:09:56.801 --> 1:09:58.237
HONEYBOY:
Simone, stop.

1:09:59.412 --> 1:10:00.587
Mitzi, don't.

1:10:01.153 --> 1:10:02.763
Mitzi, she's a mean fighter.

1:10:06.027 --> 1:10:08.552
[laughing]

1:10:08.595 --> 1:10:10.293
You look so stupid.

1:10:10.336 --> 1:10:11.598
[laughing]

1:10:11.859 --> 1:10:15.863
[quirky jazz instrumental]

1:10:17.865 --> 1:10:21.869
♪ music continues

1:10:22.261 --> 1:10:25.221
To remember the dark times.

1:10:27.135 --> 1:10:28.746
CHARLIE B:
Please don't do that.

1:10:28.789 --> 1:10:30.617
I only have a few copies.

1:10:38.277 --> 1:10:41.280
I grew up with your
horrible family all my life.

1:10:42.238 --> 1:10:43.456
[horks]

1:10:45.328 --> 1:10:49.288
[coughing]

1:10:53.640 --> 1:10:55.294
MITZI:
Get off!

1:10:59.559 --> 1:11:00.778
Get the hell out of here

1:11:00.821 --> 1:11:03.215
before I run your
whole family over!

1:11:03.259 --> 1:11:04.477
[spits]

1:11:04.695 --> 1:11:05.870
And you.

1:11:05.913 --> 1:11:06.871
Huh?

1:11:06.914 --> 1:11:08.176
You better be careful.

1:11:09.308 --> 1:11:10.527
You're lucky you're old.

1:11:10.570 --> 1:11:13.617
I can still make
your mother cry.

1:11:13.660 --> 1:11:15.532
Get the hell out of here

1:11:15.575 --> 1:11:18.099
and crawl back in the
hole you came from.

1:11:18.143 --> 1:11:19.971
Go on!
[thunderous drumming]

1:11:20.014 --> 1:11:24.018
[rhythmic drumming]

1:11:26.020 --> 1:11:30.111
♪ continues

1:11:32.897 --> 1:11:35.116
Mom, awesome.

1:11:37.380 --> 1:11:41.384
[traditional indigenous singing]

1:11:53.396 --> 1:11:58.052
♪ continues

1:12:09.063 --> 1:12:12.066
[applause and cheers]

1:12:35.133 --> 1:12:37.918
[applause echoing]

1:12:40.921 --> 1:12:43.924
[chimes twinkling]

1:12:46.927 --> 1:12:49.930
♪ continues

1:13:52.340 --> 1:13:56.780
[rhythmic drumming]

1:13:56.823 --> 1:14:01.088
[traditional indigenous singing]

1:14:03.090 --> 1:14:06.877
♪ continues

1:14:06.920 --> 1:14:10.924
[singing slows down]

1:14:22.936 --> 1:14:27.114
♪ continues

1:14:33.120 --> 1:14:37.124
[singing speeds back
up to normal speed]

1:14:43.130 --> 1:14:46.133
♪ continues

1:14:54.577 --> 1:14:58.537
[soft guitar strumming]

1:15:00.583 --> 1:15:02.454
[dishes crashing]

1:15:02.498 --> 1:15:05.892
[soft guitar strumming]

1:15:09.896 --> 1:15:14.335
♪ Where did you go, brother

1:15:16.337 --> 1:15:20.428
♪ Where have you been

1:15:23.431 --> 1:15:27.305
♪ Where did you go, brother

1:15:31.309 --> 1:15:33.703
♪ Where have you been

1:15:33.746 --> 1:15:34.921
Hey, sleepy.

1:15:36.575 --> 1:15:39.230
I brought you some books.

1:15:39.273 --> 1:15:43.103
♪ You must have seen
the bullets bright ♪

1:15:47.107 --> 1:15:51.111
♪ Watch dangers
falling from the sky ♪

1:15:55.028 --> 1:15:57.248
♪ Where did you go

1:15:57.291 --> 1:15:59.293
Mary, find a nurse right now.

1:16:02.645 --> 1:16:04.124
Help's coming.

1:16:14.091 --> 1:16:17.834
I want to get out of here.

1:16:17.877 --> 1:16:19.879
Like you wouldn't believe.

1:16:24.797 --> 1:16:27.757
I've never seen you this bad.

1:16:27.800 --> 1:16:28.975
I'm dying.

1:16:31.891 --> 1:16:33.545
It hurts.

1:16:50.083 --> 1:16:51.868
Charles Baudelaire,

1:16:52.782 --> 1:16:55.001
"The Eyes of Beauty".

1:16:55.045 --> 1:16:57.787
You are a sky of autumn,

1:16:57.830 --> 1:16:59.832
pale and rose.

1:17:00.746 --> 1:17:04.620
But all the sea of sadness in
my blood surges and ebbing,

1:17:06.230 --> 1:17:08.232
leaves my lips morose.

1:17:10.364 --> 1:17:13.367
Salts with the memory
of the bitter flood.

1:17:13.890 --> 1:17:18.634
♪ Where did you go, my brother ♪

1:17:21.288 --> 1:17:26.076
♪ So long you were gone

1:17:29.470 --> 1:17:33.649
♪ You saw the quiet
water bleed ♪

1:17:33.692 --> 1:17:36.521
Charity's been here.

1:17:36.564 --> 1:17:41.308
♪ Where soldiers go
and never leave ♪

1:17:45.878 --> 1:17:47.575
Stay strong, Charles.

1:17:48.185 --> 1:17:51.841
Try to relax.
I'll be right back.

1:17:51.884 --> 1:17:56.367
♪ My brother

1:17:56.410 --> 1:18:00.414
♪ So long you were gone

1:18:02.721 --> 1:18:04.549
You gotta get better.

1:18:05.637 --> 1:18:09.597
♪ One by one the
warriors come around ♪

1:18:12.731 --> 1:18:14.951
I'm not going anywhere.

1:18:15.995 --> 1:18:20.260
♪ It's time to lay
your quiver down ♪

1:18:21.348 --> 1:18:24.874
I'll always be here.

1:18:24.917 --> 1:18:29.922
♪ One by one the
warriors come ♪

1:18:32.795 --> 1:18:36.929
♪ It's time to lay
your quiver down ♪

1:18:38.931 --> 1:18:41.107
[crying]

1:18:41.151 --> 1:18:44.110
[flatline buzzing]

1:18:44.154 --> 1:18:48.027
♪ Duty's done,
you're free to go ♪

1:18:53.032 --> 1:18:54.338
♪ It's time to raise

1:18:54.381 --> 1:18:57.776
Why does everything
always happen to you?

1:18:57.820 --> 1:19:02.128
♪ Everybody knows

1:19:06.132 --> 1:19:10.746
♪ One by one the
warriors come ♪

1:19:13.139 --> 1:19:17.143
♪ It's time to lay
your quiver down ♪

1:19:23.410 --> 1:19:25.630
Guess who I just dropped off.

1:19:25.673 --> 1:19:26.718
Who?

1:19:26.762 --> 1:19:28.154
Mary.

1:19:28.198 --> 1:19:31.027
It's her first visit back
since school started.

1:19:31.070 --> 1:19:33.072
Who knew she was
the scholarly type?

1:19:56.574 --> 1:19:58.010
It's from Charlie B.

1:20:05.017 --> 1:20:06.845
I should take this to my Mom.

1:20:20.206 --> 1:20:22.992
ANNABELLE:
Mitzi, is that you?

1:20:23.035 --> 1:20:24.863
Yes, Momma.

1:20:24.907 --> 1:20:28.780
Something came in the
mail from Charlie.

1:20:30.434 --> 1:20:32.915
When his Mom died,

1:20:32.958 --> 1:20:34.612
I felt like dying too.

1:20:39.617 --> 1:20:41.445
And then Charlie came.

1:20:46.058 --> 1:20:48.582
I knew that he
needed all my help

1:20:48.626 --> 1:20:50.628
if he was going to survive.

1:20:55.633 --> 1:20:59.071
The love I didn't
show you went to him.

1:21:02.814 --> 1:21:06.818
It wasn't fair,
I know this.

1:21:09.952 --> 1:21:11.823
But you are strong.

1:21:20.484 --> 1:21:21.702
Charlie.

1:21:26.620 --> 1:21:31.625
I barely knew how to love
after what life gave me.

1:21:36.108 --> 1:21:39.155
And what little I had,

1:21:39.198 --> 1:21:42.201
I didn't know how to stretch
it out for everybody.

1:21:44.334 --> 1:21:45.813
Mom, it's okay.

1:21:47.119 --> 1:21:49.948
ANNABELLE:
I became hard and hateful.

1:21:51.558 --> 1:21:54.431
That damn school took
everything from me.

1:21:54.474 --> 1:21:57.303
I don't know how William stayed with me all these years.

1:21:58.565 --> 1:22:02.526
MITZI:
Mom, the hospital sent
over Charlie B's things.

1:22:02.569 --> 1:22:03.962
He left something for you.

1:22:08.010 --> 1:22:09.794
Dear Auntie Annabelle,

1:22:09.837 --> 1:22:11.970
if you have this letter
in your possession,

1:22:12.014 --> 1:22:16.018
you know I am no longer
amongst the living.

1:22:16.061 --> 1:22:18.803
Thank you for making me
a place in your home,

1:22:18.846 --> 1:22:20.196
and in your heart.

1:22:22.328 --> 1:22:26.289
With this letter I'm
sending cedar shavings

1:22:26.332 --> 1:22:29.335
discarded while a friend of
mine carved a ceremonial mask.

1:22:32.860 --> 1:22:35.254
I watched him from the
beginning to the end.

1:22:36.038 --> 1:22:37.648
These were sacrificed
for beauty,

1:22:37.691 --> 1:22:39.693
but they are just as powerful.

1:22:41.434 --> 1:22:43.871
I slept with them
under my pillow.

1:22:43.915 --> 1:22:46.744
I remember each scrape
and end of that chisel.

1:22:50.269 --> 1:22:52.141
They were given to me,

1:22:52.184 --> 1:22:54.491
and now I give them
to you, Auntie.

1:22:54.534 --> 1:22:56.841
With deep, deep love

1:22:56.884 --> 1:22:59.322
and utmost affection,

1:22:59.365 --> 1:23:00.845
Charles Bearclaw.

1:23:00.888 --> 1:23:04.892
[sombre guitar strumming]

1:23:12.900 --> 1:23:16.165
♪ continues

1:23:16.208 --> 1:23:19.211
[sombre humming]

1:23:40.232 --> 1:23:44.628
♪ continues

1:24:00.296 --> 1:24:03.603
WILLIAM:
I knew we, we had
to go sometime.

1:24:03.647 --> 1:24:06.041
I don't think we can
spend another winter here,

1:24:06.084 --> 1:24:07.477
especially now.

1:24:07.520 --> 1:24:09.522
MITZI:
Dad, come and eat a sandwich.

1:24:45.645 --> 1:24:47.299
Happy birthday, Mitzi.

1:25:00.921 --> 1:25:02.271
Hm.

1:25:02.314 --> 1:25:03.707
20 bucks, thanks, Dad.

1:25:05.709 --> 1:25:07.319
You're a big girl now.

1:25:09.191 --> 1:25:12.019
This past year has
gone by so fast.

1:25:12.890 --> 1:25:14.892
I can't believe you're 26.

1:25:23.205 --> 1:25:24.989
You'll like living
in town, Dad.

1:25:25.032 --> 1:25:26.295
Especially in the winter.

1:25:26.338 --> 1:25:30.081
You'll get to visit Molly,
Blabby, grandkids.

1:25:30.386 --> 1:25:31.952
They'll be glad to see you.

1:25:36.435 --> 1:25:38.263
Maybe I'll take up tennis.

1:25:39.351 --> 1:25:42.006
[laughing]

1:25:42.049 --> 1:25:43.312
Can't see it.

1:25:43.355 --> 1:25:44.791
You're right.

1:25:45.096 --> 1:25:47.098
Little beach volleyball though.

1:25:55.628 --> 1:25:56.890
Thanks, Dad.

1:26:01.895 --> 1:26:06.465
[soft spiritual flute music]

1:26:07.901 --> 1:26:10.600
♪ continues

1:26:13.603 --> 1:26:15.257
So this is it.

1:26:15.300 --> 1:26:16.562
Yeah.

1:26:17.476 --> 1:26:19.348
The world's waiting for me.

1:26:19.391 --> 1:26:20.784
What can I tell ya.

1:26:21.176 --> 1:26:24.570
What will Owl Island be
like without the Bearclaws?

1:26:24.614 --> 1:26:26.442
It will not be the same.

1:26:32.404 --> 1:26:34.624
Little parting gift.

1:26:34.667 --> 1:26:36.495
Do you know what this is?

1:26:38.932 --> 1:26:40.934
A nasty revenge of
Simone Muskrat.

1:26:41.674 --> 1:26:43.328
She said she'd get me.

1:26:43.763 --> 1:26:45.243
Poor Ringo.

1:26:45.287 --> 1:26:46.592
And lucky me.

1:26:46.636 --> 1:26:48.812
Word is someone got ahold
of some love medicine.

1:26:50.422 --> 1:26:51.554
Listen to this.

1:26:51.597 --> 1:26:52.903
"On this day

1:26:52.946 --> 1:26:56.080
"I will marry my
Indian princess.

1:26:56.123 --> 1:26:59.170
"Our marriage will take
place in the Poconos.

1:26:59.214 --> 1:27:03.653
"Together we are releasing
two eagles into the wild

1:27:03.696 --> 1:27:05.742
"to live together as
they were meant to be."

1:27:05.785 --> 1:27:07.004
Ugh.

1:27:07.047 --> 1:27:08.832
Where the heck do you
get two eagles from?

1:27:10.834 --> 1:27:12.401
I got a couple of dogs
I've been putting aside

1:27:12.444 --> 1:27:13.489
for my wedding.

1:27:13.532 --> 1:27:15.273
I've seen your dogs.

1:27:15.317 --> 1:27:17.667
You ain't getting
married for a long time.

1:27:17.710 --> 1:27:18.972
Okay.

1:27:19.016 --> 1:27:20.974
Dogs don't have to be
a part of the ceremony.

1:27:22.062 --> 1:27:24.064
You give in way too easily.

1:27:24.891 --> 1:27:29.679
I want dogs, cats, birds,

1:27:29.722 --> 1:27:32.159
even your relatives at
the wedding [chuckling].

1:27:35.206 --> 1:27:38.427
Pretty soon I'll be the one

1:27:38.470 --> 1:27:42.431
talking about letting
eagles loose into the wild.

1:27:42.474 --> 1:27:44.215
Something stupid like that.

1:27:44.259 --> 1:27:46.261
[low spiritual flute music]

1:27:46.304 --> 1:27:47.784
It's not that stupid.

1:27:47.827 --> 1:27:51.831
[low spiritual flute music]

1:27:53.833 --> 1:27:57.837
♪ continues

1:28:10.328 --> 1:28:13.462
I didn't want to come back.

1:28:13.505 --> 1:28:15.202
Now I don't want to leave.

1:28:18.205 --> 1:28:20.207
But I have wars to end,

1:28:21.513 --> 1:28:23.341
lives to save and

1:28:24.734 --> 1:28:26.344
things to make.

1:28:45.407 --> 1:28:47.496
WILLIAM:
Mitzi, time to go!

1:28:47.539 --> 1:28:49.585
Get Mom ready!

1:28:49.628 --> 1:28:51.238
You ready?

1:28:51.282 --> 1:28:52.457
I'm ready.

1:28:56.156 --> 1:28:57.549
She's ready!

